expected([1, 2, 3]) = Maybe 1

Test: List/MapWithDefinition
Description = morphir-elm only compiles top-level definitions to the definition form, and all local ones to lambdas.

expected(1, [2, 3]) = False

Test: List/sortBy
expected(["mouse", "cat"]) = ["cat", "mouse"]
expected(["alice", "chuck", "bobby"]) = ["alice", "chuck", "bobby"]
expected(["word"]) = ["word"]

Test: List/sort
expected([3, 2, -2, 1, 0]) = [-2, 0, 1, 2, 3]
expected([1, 1]) = [1, 1]
expected([1]) = [1]
expected([]) = []

Test: List/tail
Note: Elm's tail returns a Maybe List a, this is a departure from all
other cons-cell-derived List implementations.
expected([1, 2, 3]) = Just [2, 3]
expected([3]) = Just []
expected([]) = Nothing

Test: List/take
expected(2, [1, 2, 3]) = [1, 2]
expected(0, [1, 2, 3]) = []
expected(-1, [1, 2, 3]) = []
expected(2, []) = []

Test: Set/foldl
expected(Set(1, 2, 3)) = [3, 2, 1]
expected(Set(2, 3, 1)) = [3, 2, 1] // Set.foldl iterates in order from lowest to highest
expected(Set()) = []

Test: Set/foldr
expected(Set(1, 2, 3)) = [1, 2, 3]
expected(Set(2, 3, 1)) = [1, 2, 3] // Set.foldr iterates in order from highest to lowest
expected(Set()) = []

Test: Set/insert
expected(1, Set()) = Set(1)
expected(1, Set(2)) = Set(1, 2)
expected(1, Set(1)) = Set(1)

Test: Set/intersect
expected(Set(1, 2, 3), Set(2, 3, 4)) = Set(2, 3)
expected(Set(1, 2), Set(3, 4)) = Set()
expected(Set(), Set(1, 2)) = Set()
expected(Set(1, 2), Set()) = Set()
expected(Set(), Set()) = Set()

Test: Set/isEmpty
expected(Set(1)) = false
expected(Set()) = true

Test: Set/map
expected(Set(1, 2, 3)) = Set(2, 4, 6)
expected(Set()) = Set()

Test: Set/partition
expected(Set(1, 2, 3)) = (Set(1), Set(2, 3))
expected(Set(0, 1)) = (Set(0, 1), Set())
expected(Set(2, 3)) = (Set(), Set(2, 3))
expected(Set()) = (Set(), Set())

Test: Set/remove
expected(2, Set(1, 2, 3)) = Set(1, 3)
expected(2, Set(1)) = Set(1)
expected(2, Set()) = Set()

Test: Set/union
expected(Set(1), Set(2)) = Set(1, 2)
expected(Set(1, 2), Set(2, 3)) = Set(1, 2, 3)
expected(Set(), Set(1, 2)) = Set(1, 2)
expected(Set(1, 2), Set()) = Set(1, 2)
expected(Set(), Set()) = Set()
